xubamp (0.2.2-1) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Analyzer/peak falloff is frame-rate independent: a falloff setting
    now means the same thing at every refresh rate, fixing the glitchy
    look of fast falloffs at high fps.
  * The windowshade title scrolls like the original instead of sitting
    clipped mid-glyph.
  * The playlist's selected/total readout sits left-anchored in its
    classic recess and never cuts its last digit; the baked mini
    transport row under it is clickable.
  * The Visualization preferences page no longer overlaps its header.
  * FLAC and Ogg Vorbis are declared in the desktop file, AppStream
    metadata, man page, and package description, so "Open with xubamp"
    now appears for those files.
  * Internal: dead-code audit applied; the workspace is clippy-clean.

 -- Hector Oviedo <hector.ernesto.oviedo@gmail.com>  Thu, 17 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000

